- It's in English.

6
00:05:09,493 --> 00:05:10,774
- I have a dictionary.

7
00:05:10,862 --> 00:05:11,709
- Very good.

8
00:05:11,729 --> 00:05:12,576
Give it a go.

9
00:05:12,596 --> 00:05:13,443
- Thank you.

10
00:05:31,799 --> 00:05:32,955
- Knock it off.

11
00:05:32,975 --> 00:05:34,131
- Butt out!

12
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:35,809
Better get going.

13
00:05:35,835 --> 00:05:37,644
Jiro...

14
00:05:38,463 --> 00:05:40,272
No more bullying, okay?

15
00:05:57,648 --> 00:06:00,458
You look quite the hero.

16
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:02,836
I slipped and fell.

17
00:06:03,414 --> 00:06:04,862
- Fighting is never justified.

18
00:06:04,882 --> 00:06:06,330
- I know.

19
00:06:07,450 --> 00:06:09,593
Go have your snack.

20
00:06:10,203 --> 00:06:11,344
Thank you.

21
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:15,515
Big brother, you're back!

22
00:06:17,011 --> 00:06:18,980
I was waiting for you.

23
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,969
Let's pick bamboo grass.

24
00:06:22,423 --> 00:06:23,982
Big brother!

25
00:06:26,969 --> 00:06:29,529
I want to pick bamboo grass.

26
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:36,703
You promised to go with me.

27
00:06:36,771 --> 00:06:38,079
I've got homework.

28
00:06:44,487 --> 00:06:46,296
That's not homework.

29
00:06:46,364 --> 00:06:47,839
It's an English magazine.

30
00:06:51,119 --> 00:06:52,844
What a stupid moustache.

31
00:06:53,204 --> 00:06:55,889
He's a famous Italian aircraft designer.

32
00:06:56,092 --> 00:06:58,394
His name is Caproni.

33
00:06:58,414 --> 00:07:00,716
It says he's a count.

34
00:07:00,805 --> 00:07:02,398
- Your face is scratched.

35
00:07:02,418 --> 00:07:04,011
- Leave it alone.

36
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:06,858
I better put some iodine on it.

37
00:07:06,884 --> 00:07:08,902
Would you be quiet?

38
00:07:19,605 --> 00:07:22,082
Big brother, what are you doing?

39
00:07:22,191 --> 00:07:23,917
You're not allowed up here.

40
00:07:23,985 --> 00:07:25,585
You're not wearing glasses.

41
00:07:25,611 --> 00:07:30,090
Focusing on the stars should improve my eyesight.

42
00:07:31,669 --> 00:07:33,200
- Mother will scold you.

43
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:34,751
- A shooting star!

44
00:07:36,038 --> 00:07:37,847
There's another one.

45
00:07:39,010 --> 00:07:40,135
They're pretty.

46
00:07:40,155 --> 00:07:41,280
See?

47
00:07:41,300 --> 00:07:42,425
Like that.

48
00:07:43,671 --> 00:07:45,939
There's so many of them.

49
00:08:23,211 --> 00:08:25,145
I'm a Japanese boy.

50
00:08:30,092 --> 00:08:33,445
I think this is my dream.

51
00:08:49,862 --> 00:08:52,505
This is my dream, you know.

52
00:08:52,615 --> 00:08:54,424
It's mine too.

53
00:08:54,533 --> 00:08:56,009
Your dream?

54
00:08:56,087 --> 00:08:58,368
Listen, Japanese boy.

55
00:08:58,388 --> 00:09:00,669
You think we are sharing this dream?

56
00:09:00,957 --> 00:09:02,015
It's strange.

57
00:09:02,093 --> 00:09:04,291
You're Count Caproni, aren't you?

58
00:09:04,311 --> 00:09:06,509
I'm very glad to meet you.

59
00:09:07,765 --> 00:09:09,224
Interesting.

60
00:09:09,244 --> 00:09:10,703
Yes, this is a dream.

61
00:09:10,723 --> 00:09:12,182
This world is a dream.

62
00:09:12,426 --> 00:09:14,194
Welcome to my kingdom.

63
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:15,862
I'm honored.

64
00:09:17,139 --> 00:09:18,865
Look at them.

65
00:09:24,031 --> 00:09:26,062
They will bomb the enemy city.

66
00:09:26,082 --> 00:09:28,113
Most of them won't return.

67
00:09:34,949 --> 00:09:37,384
But the war will soon be over.

68
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:48,228
Climb up, Japanese boy.

69
00:09:50,099 --> 00:09:52,506
This is my dream.

70
00:09:52,526 --> 00:09:54,933
When the war is over, I will build this.

71
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:58,863
Magnificent, isn't she?

72
00:09:59,765 --> 00:10:00,907
Let's fly.

73
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:07,664
Instead of bombs, she'll carry passengers.

74
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:19,592
Of course we can't climb up here...

75
00:10:19,712 --> 00:10:21,222
but dreams are convenient.

76
00:10:21,242 --> 00:10:22,752
One can go anywhere.

77
00:10:30,264 --> 00:10:32,108
Come, join me.

78
00:10:32,128 --> 00:10:33,972
You can walk along the spar.

79
00:10:38,596 --> 00:10:40,280
Take a look.

80
00:11:15,393 --> 00:11:17,341
- She's beautiful, no?

81
00:11:17,361 --> 00:11:19,309
- Yes, incredible.

82
00:11:23,724 --> 00:11:27,577
She'll carry a hundred people across the Atlantic.

83
00:11:29,490 --> 00:11:30,254
Mr.

84
00:11:30,274 --> 00:11:31,038
Caproni?

85
00:11:31,058 --> 00:11:31,822
I have a question.

86
00:11:33,567 --> 00:11:36,336
Do you think I could design airplanes?

87
00:11:38,666 --> 00:11:40,239
I'll never be a pilot.

88
00:11:40,259 --> 00:11:41,832
I'm too nearsighted.

89
00:11:43,244 --> 00:11:45,512
Listen, Japanese boy.

90
00:11:45,631 --> 00:11:47,308
I'm not a pilot.

91
00:11:47,328 --> 00:11:49,005
I don't even know how to fly.

92
00:11:50,251 --> 00:11:53,019
To fly airplanes is simple.

93
00:11:53,347 --> 00:11:55,546
But I am a creator of airplanes.

94
00:11:55,566 --> 00:11:57,765
An aeronautical engineer!

95
00:11:58,217 --> 00:11:59,317
Yes!

96
00:11:59,468 --> 00:12:01,694
Listen to me, Japanese boy.

97
00:12:01,814 --> 00:12:03,991
Airplanes are not tools for war.

98
00:12:04,011 --> 00:12:06,188
They are not for making money.

99
00:12:06,475 --> 00:12:08,868
Airplanes are beautiful dreams.

100
00:12:08,936 --> 00:12:12,163
Engineers turn dreams into reality.

101
00:12:12,606 --> 00:12:13,665
Yes!

102
00:12:13,868 --> 00:12:15,316
Arrivederci.

103
00:12:15,336 --> 00:12:16,784
We'll meet again.

104
00:12:30,749 --> 00:12:34,060
Jiro, you should go to bed.

105
00:12:35,139 --> 00:12:37,504
You startled me.

106
00:12:37,524 --> 00:12:39,889
I heard you talking to someone.

107
00:12:40,634 --> 00:12:43,403
Mother, I'm going to be an aeronautical engineer.

108
00:12:43,481 --> 00:12:44,929
Really?

109
00:12:44,949 --> 00:12:46,397
That's a wonderful dream.

110
00:12:46,775 --> 00:12:48,452
Airplanes are beautiful dreams.

111
00:12:48,472 --> 00:12:50,149
That's what he told me.

112
00:12:50,311 --> 00:12:52,704
I want to design beautiful airplanes.

113
00:13:21,727 --> 00:13:22,882
You, there.

114
00:13:22,902 --> 00:13:24,057
Come, take my seat.

115
00:13:24,136 --> 00:13:25,278
Pardon me.

116
00:13:25,346 --> 00:13:26,529
Please.

117
00:14:02,424 --> 00:14:04,817
The wind feels wonderful.

118
00:14:05,302 --> 00:14:07,737
Miss, you'll lose your hat.

119
00:14:07,805 --> 00:14:08,988
Don't worry, Kinu.

120
00:14:17,606 --> 00:14:18,998
Watch out!

121
00:14:22,236 --> 00:14:23,336
Are you all right?

122
00:14:23,487 --> 00:14:25,129
Safe!

123
00:14:25,531 --> 00:14:26,964
Nice play.

124
00:14:27,908 --> 00:14:29,050
Thank you.

