The well's almost dry.

161
00:19:53,939 --> 00:19:55,240
What about you?

162
00:19:55,319 --> 00:19:56,502
Thank you.

163
00:20:02,326 --> 00:20:04,635
The fire hasn't reached Ueno.

164
00:20:04,671 --> 00:20:05,994
I'm heading for the university.

165
00:20:06,014 --> 00:20:07,337
What about you?

166
00:20:07,414 --> 00:20:09,515
I'll bring someone from home.

167
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:11,851
I'll go with you.

168
00:20:12,095 --> 00:20:13,438
- Look after this, Kinu.

169
00:20:13,458 --> 00:20:14,801
- I will.

170
00:20:14,932 --> 00:20:16,067
We'll be back soon.

171
00:20:16,087 --> 00:20:17,222
Don't worry.

172
00:20:17,799 --> 00:20:19,608
Watch my suitcase.

173
00:21:40,851 --> 00:21:42,299
- Thank you.

174
00:21:42,319 --> 00:21:43,767
- I'll leave her to you.

175
00:21:43,927 --> 00:21:45,778
But what's your name?

176
00:21:50,444 --> 00:21:51,767
That was some guy.

177
00:21:51,787 --> 00:21:53,110
Don't you think, Kinu?

178
00:22:11,256 --> 00:22:12,495
Jiro!

179
00:22:12,515 --> 00:22:13,754
You picked a great day to come back.

180
00:22:13,874 --> 00:22:15,474
How bad is it, Honjo?

181
00:22:15,584 --> 00:22:18,144
The whole east side is burning.

182
00:22:20,297 --> 00:22:22,565
That's everything we could carry.

183
00:22:22,632 --> 00:22:24,108
Got a smoke?

184
00:22:29,566 --> 00:22:30,900
A flying door?

185
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:32,254
That's just great.

186
00:22:32,274 --> 00:22:33,608
They'll never stop the fire now.

187
00:22:33,727 --> 00:22:35,452
Tokyo's finished.

188
00:22:49,795 --> 00:22:51,868
He really built it.

189
00:22:51,888 --> 00:22:53,961
Caproni has giant dreams.

190
00:23:54,891 --> 00:23:56,575
Stop the camera!

191
00:24:04,911 --> 00:24:06,129
The wind's shifting.

192
00:24:06,149 --> 00:24:07,367
It's coming this way.

193
00:24:10,574 --> 00:24:14,343
Is the wind still rising, Japanese boy?

194
00:24:14,703 --> 00:24:17,388
Yes, it's a gale.

195
00:24:18,081 --> 00:24:21,517
